## Architecture Overview

```
                    ┌──────────────────────────┐
                    │     FastAPI (Port 8119)   │
                    │                          │
  POST /api/report/generate  ──►  LangGraph Workflow  ──►  JSON Response
  POST /api/report/ageing    ──►  ETL Pipeline          ──►  Status Dict
  GET  /api/health           ──►  Health Check          ──►  {"status":"ok"}
                    │                          │
                    └──────┬───────────┬───────┘
                           │           │
                    ┌──────▼──────┐ ┌──▼──────────────┐
                    │  Oracle ERP  │ │    MariaDB      │
                    │  (Supplier   │ │  (Reporting     │
                    │   Invoices)  │ │   Tables)       │
                    └─────────────┘ └─────────────────┘
                           │
                    ┌──────▼──────────────┐
                    │  AI Gateway (qwen)│
                    │  llmgw.datapatterns │
                    └─────────────────────┘
```

**Key Design Principles:**

- **Read-only queries only** — SQL validator blocks all DML (UPDATE, DELETE, DROP, INSERT, ALTER, TRUNCATE, EXEC, MERGE)
- **Whitelist-based table/column access** — Only 6 Oracle ERP tables and their defined columns are accessible
- **Self-correcting generation** — LLM retries up to 3 times with validation errors appended to the prompt
- **Two modes**: Interactive (per-query pipeline via API) and Batch (ETL for the ageing report)
- **Connection pooling** — SQLAlchemy engines for both Oracle and MariaDB with `pool_size=5, max_overflow=10`

