### ERD vs ERD_RICH

Two levels of metadata exist:

- **`ERD`** — Compact table-level schema injected into the LLM prompt (`{runtime_schema}`). Contains column names, types, PK/FK flags.
- **`ERD_RICH`** — Full column-level descriptions, nullable flags, allowed values, formulas, business context, and join paths. Used ONLY by the deterministic SQL validator. Not sent to the LLM to keep the prompt compact.

