## Security Considerations

1. **Read-only enforcement** — The SQL validator blocks all DML statements at the regex level
2. **Whitelist access** — Only the 6 defined Oracle ERP tables and their columns are accessible
3. **Row limit** — Queries are capped at 10,000 rows to prevent memory exhaustion
4. **No user input in SQL** — The LLM generates static SQL; user input is a natural language description, never interpolated into the query
5. **Prompt injection guard** — The system prompt explicitly forbids generating non-SELECT statements
6. **AI gateway authentication** — All LLM calls are routed through the internal gateway with API key authentication
